o alumni educate and build skills critical to career success view mba student events » the biennial marketing insights at chicago booth conference brings together corporate partners alumni and booth faculty the conference features research collaborations between booth faculty and marketing practitioners booth faculty share research that relies on marketing data and generates valuable consumer insights relevant to a range of companies and business professionals industry practitioners complement the presentations by offering a discussion of potential applications and real world discernments the next conference will be held spring  presentations featured at the marketing insights  include   advertising in health insurance markets brad shapiro assistant professor of marketing discussant brett edelson vice president unitedhealthcare community and state   scalable price targeting sanjog misra charles h kellstadt professor of marketing and neubauer family faculty fellow industry discussant dan cropsey head of data solutionscatalina marketing demand for “healthy” products false claims in advertising anita rao assistant professor of marketing industry discussant gary singer partner cmo atkearney   examining the effect of numeric cues on consumer behavior abigail sussman assistant professor of marketing dan bartels assistant professor of marketing industry discussant eli strick director of marketing strategy and planning united airlines   consumer information and the branded versus private label tradeoff jeanpierre dubé sigmund e edelstone professor of marketing industry discussant james dodge senior consultant milliman james m kilts  executive bio compensation history and contacts  equilar atlas   log in  sign up x   as featured in james m kilts board member at metlife inc view full profile are you james m kilts claim your profile   sign up for equilar atlas and view james m kiltss full profile with equilar atlas you can identify corporate executives in james m kiltss networ